Additional Terms for the Seen Language Implementation:

1. COMMERCIAL USE: Commercial use of this software is explicitly permitted 
   and encouraged, including but not limited to:
   - Building commercial applications using the Seen language
   - Distributing the Seen compiler as part of commercial products
   - Using Seen in enterprise and proprietary software development
   - Selling products or services built with or incorporating Seen

2. CONTRIBUTIONS: Contributions to this project are welcomed under the 
   following terms:
   - All contributions become part of this project under the same MIT License
   - Contributors retain copyright to their original contributions
   - By contributing, you grant the project maintainer(s) perpetual rights
     to use, modify, and distribute your contributions
   - Contributors are encouraged to be credited in project documentation

3. ATTRIBUTION: While not legally required under MIT License, attribution
   is appreciated when:
   - Using substantial portions of the compiler implementation
   - Creating derivative programming languages based on Seen
   - Publishing research or articles about techniques used in Seen

4. FAIR USE OF PROJECT NAME: 
   While you may create derivative works, please be respectful and:
   - Avoid creating competing languages that use the exact name "Seen" 
     in a way that would confuse users
   - If creating derivatives, clearly indicate they are based on or 
     inspired by this project
   - Give appropriate credit when building upon this work

This license is designed to:
✓ Allow free commercial use of Seen language
